This paper deals with the spectrum sharing problem in a cognitive radio network, which involves information theory (IT) and game theory (GT) concepts. The use of RF signals to power the secondary user's transmission also involves networked systems (NI) and signal processing (SY) techniques. Additionally, the paper mentions simulation results, which could fall under multimedia (MM) category. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IT and cs.GT, followed by cs.NI, cs.SY, and cs.MM.
